I don't want to get hung up on helmets being

635
00:59:29,086 --> 00:59:31,148
the be all and end all of bike safety.

636
00:59:31,248 --> 00:59:34,170
I know that they absolutely do what they are supposed to do.

637
00:59:34,270 --> 00:59:38,293
And I have cracked a helmet myself more than once.

638
00:59:40,435 --> 00:59:42,056
And I wear one every day.

639
00:59:43,037 --> 00:59:48,341
But ultimately, we are they're not required by law.

640
00:59:49,122 --> 00:59:52,885
And I think our bigger priority should be in preventing crashes.

641
00:59:54,046 --> 00:59:56,648
The helmet is the is the

642
00:59:57,992 --> 01:00:04,353
last resort for mitigating the worst effects when everything else has already gone wrong.

643
01:00:06,234 --> 01:00:17,676
And I think we have enough to do with all of the other things that could possibly go wrong, but I don't think we need to split hairs about blue bikes and helmets.

644
01:00:18,216 --> 01:00:22,857
I'm all for distributing helmets, but I think this is a silly thing to get hung up on all things considered.

645
01:00:27,962 --> 01:00:29,463
Sounds a little New Hampshire like.

646
01:00:30,003 --> 01:00:30,344
All right.

647
01:00:31,084 --> 01:00:35,667
Well, I mean, we're, we're still only Medford and

648
01:00:37,037 --> 01:00:40,178
We can still only give people helmets and encourage them to wear them.

649
01:00:40,218 --> 01:00:44,399
We are not going to change state law to require them for everybody all the time.

650
01:00:44,419 --> 01:00:57,803
The last couple of times I saw people on blue bikes who clearly were not bike riders and using it for convenience, they seemed to be really nonchalant and not paying attention.

651
01:00:58,783 --> 01:01:01,485
granted they're on a 70 or 60 pound bike.

652
01:01:01,886 --> 01:01:07,451
It's a bit treating it almost like a taxi with a little bit of regard to safety.

653
01:01:07,491 --> 01:01:15,618
And I thought, wow, these people really need helmets because they're a little riper for a crash than a true bicyclist is.

654
01:01:15,978 --> 01:01:16,518
Maybe so.

655
01:01:16,559 --> 01:01:25,366
But for whatever it's worth, I think the the number of fatalities on bike share bikes nationwide is actually surprisingly low.

656
01:01:25,386 --> 01:01:25,466
Good.

657
01:01:27,289 --> 01:01:27,929
Very, very low.

